<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 5:45AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IS IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON EST TODAY...
A widely scattered region of freezing rain has redeveloped and
will impact Saginaw and up into the northern Thumb through the
morning hours. While temperatures now range between 33 to 35
degrees, a drop to or slightly below freezing is expected with the
onset of precipitation. This will allow precipitation to freeze
on contact on untreated roadways and surfaces. Drivers are urged
to prepare for icy roads and pedestrians should be prepared for
icy paved surfaces.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
